\title{Rational Canonical Form of a Matrix}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-19}
\taxon{definition}
\def\RCF{\mathop{\textrm{RCF}}\nolimits}

\p{Let #{\FF} be a field, let #{X\in\Mat_{n}(\FF)} be an #{n\times n} matrix over #{\FF}. The \define{Rational Canonical Form} of #{X} is the block diagonal matrix consisting of [companion matrices](ra-0053) of the [invariant factors](ra-0054) of #{X}.}

\p{We will write #{\RCF(X)} for the rational canonical form matrix of #{X}.}